The paper deals with the computational complexity of computing problem kernels in parallel, which is a topic closely related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves analyzing the structure of circuits needed to compute kernels, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses specific parameterized problems such as vertex cover, feedback vertex set, and matching, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
